                                "byte_start": 104745,
                                "byte_stop": 134316,
                                "text": "Justice Alito has our opinion in case 07-320, Davis versus Federal Election Commission."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 7.388,
                        "stop": 222.615,
                        "byte_start": 134316,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15068,
                            "name": "Samuel A. Alito, Jr.",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/samuel_alito_jr",
                            "last_name": "Alito",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2712,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 1138687200,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "George W. Bush",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2712"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32684,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 44799,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/samuel_a_alito_jr_1.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 3531,
                            "identifier": "samuel_alito_jr"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 7.388,
                                "stop": 12.574,
                                "byte_start": 134316,
                                "byte_stop": 155109,
                                "text": "And this case comes to us on appeal from United States District Court for the District of Columbia."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 12.574,
                                "stop": 21.955,
                                "byte_start": 155109,
                                "byte_stop": 192621,
                                "text": "Federal campaign finance law limits the contributions to candidates for the House of Representatives may receive from individuals and political parties."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 21.955,
                                "stop": 26.034,
                                "byte_start": 192621,
                                "byte_stop": 208921,
                                "text": "These limits generally apply equally to all candidates."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 26.034,
                                "stop": 36.912,
                                "byte_start": 208921,
                                "byte_stop": 252494,
                                "text": "However, Section 319 of the Bipartisan Campaign Reform Act of 2002, part of the so-called, \u201cMillionaires Amendment,\u201d departs from this general rule."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 36.912,
                                "stop": 45.981,
                                "byte_start": 252494,
                                "byte_stop": 288752,
                                "text": "When a self-financing candidate spends more than $350,000 of personal funds and certain other conditions are met."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 45.981,
                                "stop": 54.139,
                                "byte_start": 288752,
                                "byte_stop": 321352,
                                "text": "Section 319(a) expands the normal contribution limits but only for the candidate\u0027s non-self-financing opponent."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 54.139,
                                "stop": 68.886,
                                "byte_start": 321352,
                                "byte_stop": 380389,
                                "text": "To make it possible to tell when this -- a symmetrical regime applies, Section 319(b) requires the self-financing candidate to disclose certain information about his or her personal campaign expenditures."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 68.886,
                                "stop": 81.207,
                                "byte_start": 380389,
                                "byte_stop": 429604,
                                "text": "Appellant Jack Davis, a candidate for the House in 2004 and 2006 challenged the constitutionality of Sections 319(a) and (b)."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 81.207,
                                "stop": 89.387,
                                "byte_start": 429604,
                                "byte_stop": 462309,
                                "text": "A three-judge panel with the District Court concluded that Davis had standing but rejected his challenge on the merits, and Davis appealed to this Court."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 89.387,
                                "stop": 93.89,
                                "byte_start": 462309,
                                "byte_stop": 480386,
                                "text": "We agree that Davis possesses spending and that his claims are not moved."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 93.89,
                                "stop": 101.757,
                                "byte_start": 480386,
                                "byte_stop": 511837,
                                "text": "However, we conclude that Sections 319(a) and (b) violate the First Amendment and we therefore reverse the judgment of the District Court."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 101.757,
                                "stop": 113.177,
                                "byte_start": 511837,
                                "byte_stop": 557499,
                                "text": "If Section 319(a)\u0027s expanded contribution limits were available to both self-financing and non-self-financing candidates, Davis would have no constitutional claim."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 113.177,
                                "stop": 133.633,
                                "byte_start": 557499,
                                "byte_stop": 639315,
                                "text": "By expanding contribution limits only for non-self-financing candidates however, Section 319 (a) burdens the self-financing candidate\u0027s right in the words of Buckley versus Valeo to spend personal funds to, \u0022vigorously and tirelessly advocate his own election.\u0022"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 133.633,
                                "stop": 148.125,
                                "byte_start": 639315,
                                "byte_stop": 697307,
                                "text": "Section 319(a) does this because if a candidate vigorously exercises the right to use personal funds for campaign speech that candidate\u0027s opponent obtains substantial and unprecedented fund raising advantages."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 148.125,
                                "stop": 151.489,
                                "byte_start": 697307,
                                "byte_stop": 710786,
                                "text": "This burden is not justified by any compelling state interest."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 151.489,
                                "stop": 161.069,
                                "byte_start": 710786,
                                "byte_stop": 749029,
                                "text": "Reliance on personal funds rather than campaign contributions reduces, rather than increases the threat of corruption and perception of corruption."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 161.069,
                                "stop": 174.315,
                                "byte_start": 749029,
                                "byte_stop": 802110,
                                "text": "And we have never recognized the interest that the Government has asserted in defending the constitutionality of this provision, that is an interest in leveling electoral opportunities as a legitimate Government interest."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 174.315,
                                "stop": 182.127,
                                "byte_start": 802110,
                                "byte_stop": 833352,
                                "text": "Endorsing that interest would have ominous implications for voter\u0027s authority to evaluate the strengths of candidates for public office."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 182.127,
                                "stop": 193.868,
                                "byte_start": 833352,
                                "byte_stop": 880268,
                                "text": "Because Section 319(a)\u0027s asymmetrical contribution regime imposes a significant burden on First Amendment rights that is not justified by a compelling state interest that cannot withstand First Amendment scrutiny."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 193.868,
                                "stop": 206.514,
                                "byte_start": 880268,
                                "byte_stop": 930841,
                                "text": "And because Section 319(b)\u0027s disclosure requirements exist merely to implement Section 319(a)\u0027s unconstitutional regime to burden those requirements, imposes likewise unwarranted."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 206.514,
                                "stop": 214.661,
                                "byte_start": 930841,
                                "byte_stop": 963442,
                                "text": "Justice Stevens has filed an opinion concurring in part and dissenting in part which Justice Souter, Justice Ginsburg, and Justice Breyer have joined in part."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 214.661,
                                "stop": 222.615,
                                "byte_start": 963442,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Ginsburg has filed an opinion concurring in part and dissenting in part which Justice Breyer has joined."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
